Key Match Events: James Harden hit go-ahead free throws with 17.9 seconds left.
Ivica Zubac won the tip back to Harden, who made two more free throws with less than two seconds remaining.
CJ McCollum shot from half court and hit the front rim.
Zubac finished with 20 points and 16 rebounds.
McCollum hit eight 3s and led New Orleans with 33 points.
Trey Murphy's 3 made it 59-45 late in the second quarter.
Dejounte Murray had 13 points, 10 rebounds and six steals.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Officials prematurely blew the whistle because they thought Missi's foul shot missed the rim.
The Clippers converted 14 offensive rebounds into 20 second-chance points.
The Clippers had advantages of 40-35 in rebounding, 56-44 in paint points and 21-11 in made free throws.
The Pelicans hit a season-best 18 3s in a game.
